cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper investigates the performance of DNNs on class-incremental visual problems, which are related to machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses DNN models, which are a type of neural network, indicating a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the models using a new evaluation procedure, which involves model selection and retraining control, suggesting a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
